gomodel:SYNGO_2580  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: TARP γ-4 modulates the decay of synaptic AMPAR currents.\n\nFig. 7: Overexpression of stargazin (stg, TARP γ-2) or TARP γ-4 in cultured cerebellar granule cells from stg mutant (stg/stg) mice restored AMPAR-mediated synaptic responses. The amplitude and frequency of mEPSCs in stg/stg cells transfected with TARP γ-4 were ~50% of WT. The decay of mEPSCs and weighted decay constants were slower in TARP γ-4 expressing neurons compared to TARP γ-2 or WT cells.\n\nThe differential slowing of the decay of mEPSCs by TARP γ-4 in neurons was similar to its effect on slowing of deactivation decays for GluR1 channels in heterologous cells, \"demonstrating that the isoform-specific modulation of gating kinetics characterized here is relevant to synaptic transmission in neurons.\". Experimental description: From \"EXPERIMENTAL PROCEDURES\"\n\nStudies on Recombinant Channels: tsA201 cells were maintained and transfected as previously described (Robert and Howe, 2003). All GluR plasmids used were flip splice variants. Both Q and R variants of GluR2 were used as indicated. Individual GluR and TARP clones were cotransfected at ratios of 1:2 to 1:5. In the GluR1-GluR2 coexpression experiments, the flip version of GluR2- R was employed, and equal amounts of the two GluR plasmids were transfected....\n\nSynaptic Currents in Transfected Cerebellar Granule Cells: Stargazer mice were obtained from Jackson Laboratory...Heterozygous male and female mice were mated to obtain wild-type and homozygous stargazer mice. Cerebellar granule cell cultures were prepared from postnatal day 7 (P7) wild-type and homozygous stargazer mice as described (Losi et al., 2003)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2580" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

